WEBVTT

00:04.879 --> 00:06.423
Previously on "Magnum PI"...

00:06.464 --> 00:08.341
Magnum: There's really no man
that had more of an impact

00:08.383 --> 00:09.843
on my life than Greene.

00:09.884 --> 00:11.011
He put the team together.

00:11.052 --> 00:12.345
You're gonna
give me their names

00:12.387 --> 00:15.348
so we can hunt them down
and kill them.

00:15.390 --> 00:18.393
Seven years ago, Greene sent us
into a terrorist stronghold

00:18.435 --> 00:21.855
to take out a high-value target
named Ahmad Hadid.

00:21.896 --> 00:25.608
It appears whoever killed Greene
wants revenge for that raid,

00:25.650 --> 00:28.528
and he's willing to go
to great lengths to get it.

00:28.570 --> 00:30.363
Cane: Guy calling the shots'
name is Swayzak.

00:30.405 --> 00:31.823
He was hired to
put together the team.

00:31.865 --> 00:33.533
These guys are ex-military,
all right?

00:33.575 --> 00:35.535
Highly trained
and extremely dangerous.

00:35.577 --> 00:36.995
All right?
It'd be better for everybody

00:37.037 --> 00:38.705
if you just stepped away
from this one.

00:38.747 --> 00:41.583
Magnum, they know.
The mercs ID'd you.

00:43.752 --> 00:45.879
TC: Island Hoppers.

00:45.920 --> 00:51.676
**

00:51.718 --> 00:53.303
Oh!

00:53.762 --> 00:55.388
TC.

00:55.430 --> 00:57.682
[ Light buzzing ]

01:00.018 --> 01:01.186
[ Gasping softly ]

01:01.227 --> 01:03.688
[ Footsteps approaching ]

01:03.730 --> 01:10.570
**

01:10.612 --> 01:17.535
**

01:17.577 --> 01:19.829
[ Gunshot ]

01:19.871 --> 01:27.045
**

01:27.087 --> 01:29.464
Shammy: Hold on.
Hold on.

01:31.925 --> 01:34.594
TC.
TC, come on.

01:35.845 --> 01:37.097
TC, stay with me, buddy.

01:37.138 --> 01:39.516
Come on, look here.
Look at me, TC!

01:39.557 --> 01:42.102
Look at me, TC!
Stay with me.

01:42.143 --> 01:43.687
TC!

01:43.728 --> 01:46.064
[ Kettle whistling ]

01:46.106 --> 01:49.317
So, I just
add the water, right?

01:49.359 --> 01:52.445
Uh, yeah, with a splash of cream
and a teaspoon of sugar.

01:52.487 --> 01:54.114
That's how my mum made it.

01:54.155 --> 01:55.824
Stephanie Lum: Have now declared
the death a homicide.

01:55.865 --> 01:57.325
Little bit of sugar.

01:57.367 --> 01:58.660
A spokesman for
the Honolulu Police Department

01:58.702 --> 02:00.704
has confirmed that nurse
Lily Tanaka

02:00.745 --> 02:02.580
has been arrested
and charged with...

02:02.622 --> 02:04.749
I still don't understand
why you don't drink tea

02:04.791 --> 02:06.001
like every other Brit.

02:06.042 --> 02:07.085
...worked together.

02:07.127 --> 02:09.212
Hey, I'm watching that.

02:09.254 --> 02:11.297
Well, after everything
you've been through,

02:11.339 --> 02:15.802
I just think you could
use a little break.

02:15.844 --> 02:18.638
Right, fair enough.

02:18.680 --> 02:21.016
You know, um, I was thinking
maybe we could stay in

02:21.057 --> 02:22.183
and watch a movie,

02:22.225 --> 02:23.893
perhaps an old classic
or something.

02:23.935 --> 02:26.563
Now you're talking.
So what are you thinking?

02:26.604 --> 02:30.316
Uh, "Die Hard," "The Rock,"
"Pulp Fiction"?

02:30.358 --> 02:32.819
Maybe something a little bit
more romantic?

02:32.861 --> 02:34.154
Oh, "Rocky."

02:34.195 --> 02:36.239
[ Both laugh ]

02:36.281 --> 02:39.451
Okay, when I was little,
whenever I was ill,

02:39.492 --> 02:41.161
my mum would make me
malted milk,

02:41.202 --> 02:43.496
and we would watch
"Arthur."

02:43.538 --> 02:46.666
Dudley Moore made
quite an impression on me.

02:46.708 --> 02:49.127
Dudley Moore, huh?
Mm-hmm.

02:49.169 --> 02:51.129
That is a guy that I have

02:51.171 --> 02:52.505
absolutely nothing
in common with.

02:52.547 --> 02:54.007
Oh, no, I'm --
I'm aware.

02:54.049 --> 02:57.594
He was very quick-witted,
effortlessly charming.

02:57.635 --> 02:58.720
Hmm.

02:58.762 --> 03:00.930
You at least have your, uh,
good looks.

03:00.972 --> 03:02.557
[ Chuckles ]
Okay.

03:02.599 --> 03:04.434
[ Chuckles ]

03:08.396 --> 03:09.981
It's not as good
as I remember it.

03:10.023 --> 03:12.776
On second thought,
you know what would be great?

03:12.817 --> 03:17.030
Is a nice,
mature Bordeaux.

03:17.072 --> 03:18.281
Okay.
All right.

03:18.323 --> 03:19.491
I will head down
to the wine cellar.

03:19.532 --> 03:21.159
You queue up "Arthur."
All right.

03:21.201 --> 03:23.036
I'm really curious to know
what this --

03:23.078 --> 03:25.747
this guy, old Dudley Moore,
has that I don't.

03:25.789 --> 03:27.874
Well, get a pen and paper
so you can take notes.

03:27.916 --> 03:29.376
You know what?
I'm gonna let that one slide,

03:29.417 --> 03:31.795
but only because
you're recovering.

03:31.836 --> 03:33.588
Be right back.

03:38.176 --> 03:40.679
Tanaka will be arraigned
tomorrow morning.

03:40.720 --> 03:42.764
A source inside the prosecuting
attorney's office

03:42.806 --> 03:46.559
tells us that Tanaka had been
overmedicating a patient

03:46.601 --> 03:48.186
in order to keep them
under her care...

03:48.228 --> 03:50.522
[ Cellphone buzzing ]
...and that she killed Kahele

03:50.563 --> 03:52.565
to prevent him
from exposing that.

03:52.607 --> 03:54.734
A thorough investigation
into the hospital

03:54.776 --> 03:57.237
is now expected.
[ Telephone ringing ]

03:57.278 --> 04:02.909
**

04:02.951 --> 04:05.578
Rick, hi.
Sorry, um, Magnum isn't here.

04:05.620 --> 04:08.289
Higgins, TC's been shot.
They've taken him to Kings.

04:08.331 --> 04:09.582
I'm on my way there now.

04:09.624 --> 04:11.751
Oh, my God.
Uh, um, how bad is it?

04:11.793 --> 04:13.586
I'm not sure.
Shammy was with him.

04:13.628 --> 04:15.088
From what he described,

04:15.130 --> 04:16.548
shooter sounded like
a hired gun.

04:16.589 --> 04:18.133
Well, these are probably
the same guys who killed Greene.

04:18.174 --> 04:19.884
They must've ID'd you three.

04:19.926 --> 04:21.928
Exactly, which is why you need
to tell Thomas right away.

04:21.970 --> 04:23.179
Yeah.
These guys are smart.

04:23.221 --> 04:24.806
They're not --

04:24.848 --> 04:32.772
**

04:32.814 --> 04:40.780
**

04:40.822 --> 04:48.747
**

04:48.788 --> 04:56.504
**

04:56.546 --> 04:58.673
Great.
No power.

04:58.715 --> 05:01.092
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

05:03.470 --> 05:06.306
Here we are.
That's the one.

05:06.348 --> 05:14.814
**

05:14.856 --> 05:23.114
**

05:23.156 --> 05:25.241
[ Both grunting ]

05:25.283 --> 05:28.828
**

05:28.870 --> 05:30.830
Aah!

05:30.872 --> 05:40.799
**

05:40.840 --> 05:42.842
[ Grunting ]

05:42.884 --> 05:51.017
**

05:51.059 --> 05:52.519
Aah!

05:52.560 --> 06:02.112
**

06:02.153 --> 06:11.538
**

06:11.579 --> 06:12.997
[ Higgins gasps ]

06:13.039 --> 06:21.131
**

06:21.172 --> 06:29.305
**

06:29.347 --> 06:31.850
[ Glass shatters ]

06:31.891 --> 06:36.604
**

06:36.646 --> 06:38.606
That's Paul Swayzak.

06:38.648 --> 06:40.567
We ID'd him a while ago.

06:40.608 --> 06:42.152
Apparently he put together
the team that --

06:42.193 --> 06:44.904
that killed Greene
and came after us.

06:44.946 --> 06:47.407
Well, actually,
Rick called

06:47.449 --> 06:51.077
to say that
we might be in danger.

06:51.119 --> 06:53.621
Thomas, there's something
you have to know.

06:56.458 --> 06:59.085
[ Woman speaks indistinctly
over PA ]

06:59.127 --> 07:00.920
[ Cellphone rings ]

07:00.962 --> 07:03.757
Hey, they just, uh,
rushed him into surgery.

07:03.798 --> 07:05.342
Yeah, well,
what's his condition?

07:05.383 --> 07:06.718
Did they tell you
anything?

07:06.760 --> 07:10.347
No, but based on the blood loss,
it looked bad.

07:10.388 --> 07:13.099
Magnum, I'm sorry.
I --

07:13.141 --> 07:15.769
I saw the alert when the cameras
picked up the shooter.

07:15.810 --> 07:18.104
I tried to get to TC
as fast as I could, but --

07:18.146 --> 07:20.315
No, no, Shammy, stop.
It's not your fault.

07:20.357 --> 07:23.026
The hitter who shot TC
wasn't working alone.

07:23.068 --> 07:25.070
Listen, Higgins and I are gonna
meet you at the hospital,

07:25.111 --> 07:28.031
but make sure Rick stays put
until we get there.

07:28.073 --> 07:29.282
Wait, what are you
talking about?

07:29.324 --> 07:31.201
Rick isn't here.

07:31.242 --> 07:32.994
But that doesn't make sense.
W-When he called me,

07:33.036 --> 07:34.412
he said that he was heading
straight there.

07:34.454 --> 07:35.705
It can't have taken him
this long.

07:35.747 --> 07:37.540
I tried calling him
a few times.

07:37.582 --> 07:39.459
It went straight
to voicemail.

07:39.501 --> 07:43.129
**

07:43.171 --> 07:45.006
[ Engine revs ]

07:45.048 --> 07:47.133
[ Tires screech ]

07:47.175 --> 07:52.138
**

07:52.180 --> 07:55.225
How is it he never even
made it to his car?

07:55.266 --> 08:01.022
**

08:01.064 --> 08:03.316
It's Rick's keys.

08:03.358 --> 08:05.193
We're too late.

08:05.235 --> 08:13.993
**

08:14.035 --> 08:22.669
**

08:22.711 --> 08:25.463
[ Groans softly ]

08:25.505 --> 08:28.299
[ Breathing heavily ]

08:28.341 --> 08:31.928
**

08:35.598 --> 08:36.933
Higgins: Here we go.

08:36.975 --> 08:39.310
Okay, so Rick called you
at exactly 9:17 p.m.,

08:39.352 --> 08:43.606
so if I queue up the security
video to that time...

08:43.648 --> 08:45.316
Magnum: Right there.
[ Computer beeps ]

08:45.358 --> 08:52.741
**

08:52.782 --> 08:54.409
They got him.
I-I don't understand.

08:54.451 --> 08:55.869
I mean, the men who came
after you and TC

08:55.910 --> 08:57.537
were clearly
shooting to kill.

08:57.579 --> 08:59.998
Why did they
take Rick alive?

09:00.040 --> 09:01.291
The only thing
I can think of

09:01.332 --> 09:04.377
is when we raided
Hadid's compound,

09:04.419 --> 09:06.296
Rick was the one
who took the kill shot.

09:06.338 --> 09:08.715
So if this is about
avenging Hadid's murder,

09:08.757 --> 09:10.884
then maybe they want
to take their time

09:10.925 --> 09:13.053
with whoever
pulled the trigger.

09:13.094 --> 09:15.180
[ Car door slams ]

09:15.221 --> 09:23.938
**

09:23.980 --> 09:26.191
[ Bell jingles ]

09:26.232 --> 09:31.237
**

09:31.279 --> 09:33.907
Seriously?
I almost just shot you.

09:33.948 --> 09:35.325
Gordon,
what are you doing here?

09:35.367 --> 09:37.452
Well, I heard about what
happened to you guys and TC.

09:37.494 --> 09:39.454
Just wanted to make sure
you were safe.

09:39.496 --> 09:41.623
And when I couldn't get in
touch, I started looking around.

09:41.664 --> 09:44.417
Yeah, we had to dump our phones
in case we're being tracked.

09:44.459 --> 09:46.711
Wait, so you haven't heard
about Detective Childs?

09:46.753 --> 09:48.213
What about Childs?

09:48.254 --> 09:50.256
He was looking into the guys
who came after you.

09:50.298 --> 09:53.093
Tracked down a safe house
they'd been using.

09:53.134 --> 09:55.261
It was rigged
with a trip wire.

09:55.303 --> 09:57.222
Went up with Childs inside.

10:01.434 --> 10:03.561
I told him
to stay out of it.

10:03.603 --> 10:05.146
But he insisted.

10:06.898 --> 10:09.275
Ah, I should've
pushed back more.

10:09.317 --> 10:10.777
It's not your fault,
Thomas.

10:10.819 --> 10:12.445
I'm the one who gave him
that lead.

10:12.487 --> 10:14.948
Well, now you can be the one who
helps us track down his killer.

10:14.989 --> 10:16.408
All right? Now I need to know
everything you know.

10:16.449 --> 10:18.993
But we're in the dark
about who's behind this.

10:19.035 --> 10:20.537
I mean, whoever they are,

10:20.578 --> 10:22.122
they're racking up
quite the body count.

10:22.163 --> 10:24.124
So far they've taken out
Nadine Amherst,

10:24.165 --> 10:26.668
her boss at the CIA,
Captain Greene,

10:26.710 --> 10:28.128
and now Detective Childs.

10:28.169 --> 10:30.255
Sorry, Nadine who?
Nadine Amherst.

10:30.296 --> 10:33.174
She's the CIA expert
on Ahmad Hadid.

10:33.216 --> 10:34.884
Couple of months ago,
she died in a plane crash,

10:34.926 --> 10:37.012
but now it looks like
that was cover for a hit.

10:37.053 --> 10:38.888
Well, if these people
can stage a plane crash,

10:38.930 --> 10:40.181
I guess it was just
a matter of time

10:40.223 --> 10:41.808
before they uncovered
your identities.

10:41.850 --> 10:44.394
Yeah, but we're still unclear as
to how they actually did that.

10:44.436 --> 10:46.855
It doesn't really matter
unless it helps us find Rick.

10:46.896 --> 10:48.148
Right.
Wait, hold on.

10:48.189 --> 10:49.357
I just saw Rick's car
outside.

10:49.399 --> 10:50.567
I assumed
he was here with you.

10:50.608 --> 10:51.818
Afraid not.

10:51.860 --> 10:53.028
He was on his way
to the hospital.

10:53.069 --> 10:54.237
They grabbed him
in the parking lot

10:54.279 --> 10:55.780
before he could get
to his car.

10:55.822 --> 10:57.782
The car that he was loaded into
didn't have plates.

10:57.824 --> 11:00.160
It's a black Chevy Impala.

11:00.201 --> 11:01.828
We'll get a BOLO out.
Okay.

11:01.870 --> 11:04.414
In the meantime, Swayzak's
probably been processed by now,

11:04.456 --> 11:06.207
and at the moment,
he's probably our best chance

11:06.249 --> 11:09.085
at finding out
who has Rick.
Yeah.

11:10.378 --> 11:11.546
Shammy: Okay.

11:11.588 --> 11:13.173
Okay, look, as soon
as you have an update,

11:13.214 --> 11:14.799
you let me know, okay?

11:14.841 --> 11:16.217
All right.

11:16.259 --> 11:18.928
Okay, Magnum says
HPD is on it.

11:18.970 --> 11:21.222
They're doing everything
they can to find him.

11:21.264 --> 11:24.267
He was just over this morning,
dropping off Joy.

11:24.309 --> 11:25.852
Everything was fine,
and now he's missing

11:25.894 --> 11:27.729
and TC's been shot?

11:27.771 --> 11:31.191
If there's one thing I know
about Rick, he's a survivor.

11:31.232 --> 11:34.944
If anyone can pull through
something like this, it's him.

11:34.986 --> 11:36.863
Okay?
Okay.

11:36.905 --> 11:42.035
**

11:42.077 --> 11:44.037
[ Grunts ]

11:44.079 --> 11:52.504
**

11:52.545 --> 12:00.762
**

12:00.804 --> 12:09.062
**

12:09.104 --> 12:11.606
* But I gotta keep on trying*

12:11.648 --> 12:14.984
[ Banging ]

12:15.026 --> 12:16.611
[ Exciting music plays ]

12:16.653 --> 12:18.071
[ Men coughing ]

12:18.113 --> 12:20.532
[ Tires screech ]

12:20.573 --> 12:30.166
**

12:30.208 --> 12:33.878
[ Rick breathing heavily ]

12:33.920 --> 12:41.219
**

12:41.261 --> 12:44.681
[ Grunts and groans ]

12:44.723 --> 12:53.356
**

12:53.398 --> 12:55.817
[ Gunshots, glass shattering ]

12:55.859 --> 13:05.618
**

13:05.660 --> 13:07.454
Higgins: All right,
I unlocked his phone,

13:07.495 --> 13:10.415
and it looks like Swayzak was
in regular contact with someone,

13:10.457 --> 13:13.251
but the number appears to run
on a voice-over IP service.

13:13.293 --> 13:15.295
Wait,
so it can't be traced?
Not easily.

13:15.337 --> 13:17.339
If we can keep the caller
on the line long enough,

13:17.380 --> 13:19.966
I can backtrace the signal
through the anonymizing service

13:20.008 --> 13:24.012
to get the owner's
IP address and location.

13:24.054 --> 13:26.056
Care to do the honors?

13:26.097 --> 13:28.016
[ Sighs ]
Yeah.

13:28.058 --> 13:36.316
**

13:36.358 --> 13:37.650
Woman:
Where are you?

13:37.692 --> 13:38.818
Is it done?

13:38.860 --> 13:40.737
[ Computer beeping ]

13:41.905 --> 13:43.531
She's gonna hang up.

13:43.573 --> 13:45.658
I've already traced the call
through five anonymous servers.

13:45.700 --> 13:48.161
Swayzak, are you there?

13:48.203 --> 13:49.412
How many more are there?

13:49.454 --> 13:50.663
I don't know.
I just need more time.

13:50.705 --> 13:52.082
Swayzak?

13:52.123 --> 13:53.667
She's not gonna
be on much longer.

13:53.708 --> 13:55.377
Swayzak.

13:56.753 --> 13:58.338
[ Cellphone beeps off ]

13:59.547 --> 14:02.676
Well, whoever we just spoke to,
that should put her on notice.

14:02.717 --> 14:04.219
I have an idea.

14:04.260 --> 14:05.679
We can run voice-print analysis
on the recording.

14:05.720 --> 14:07.972
If there are any voice samples
in any of the databases,

14:08.014 --> 14:09.349
we should get a hit.

14:09.391 --> 14:12.018
[ Distorted voice ]
Where are you? Swayzak?

14:12.060 --> 14:14.229
Where are you?
Where are you?

14:14.270 --> 14:16.773
Where are you?
Where are you?

14:18.108 --> 14:19.484
You gotta be kidding me.

14:19.526 --> 14:21.027
Well, either we were just
talking to a ghost,

14:21.069 --> 14:23.697
or Nadine Amherst
is still very much alive.

14:23.738 --> 14:25.448
So she faked her own death.
Why would she do that?

14:25.490 --> 14:27.534
Because she wanted us to think
that she was the victim

14:27.575 --> 14:30.120
when, actually, all along,
she was behind this whole thing.

14:30.161 --> 14:34.457
Exactly.
The only question now is, why?

14:39.004 --> 14:43.133
HPD air support, this is Mike
Five Five Six Mike Hotel

14:43.174 --> 14:44.718
providing search assistance.

14:44.759 --> 14:47.429
I just finished a flyover
of H-2.

14:47.470 --> 14:49.639
No sighting of
our suspect vehicle.

14:49.681 --> 14:52.058
Moving on to Pupukea now.
Over.

14:52.100 --> 14:53.810
All right, thanks.

14:53.852 --> 14:55.311
Yeah, still no sign
of the car.

14:55.353 --> 14:56.396
Well, the department
put all available

14:56.438 --> 14:57.731
resources on the search.

14:57.772 --> 14:59.399
We also sent units over
to the registered owner

14:59.441 --> 15:00.734
of that make and model.

15:00.775 --> 15:02.444
In the meantime,
your CIA contact

15:02.485 --> 15:03.820
just e-mailed over
those files.

15:03.862 --> 15:05.739
What'd you learn?
Well, for starters,

15:05.780 --> 15:08.408
a CIA black site in Munich
was breached three days ago.

15:08.450 --> 15:10.035
Two agents were killed
in the process,

15:10.076 --> 15:11.453
but it looks like
that's how they finally

15:11.494 --> 15:12.912
uncovered your identities.

15:12.954 --> 15:15.248
They also sent over
everything that their agency had

15:15.290 --> 15:16.750
on Nadine Amherst,

15:16.791 --> 15:18.460
including a list of every asset
she cultivated,

15:18.501 --> 15:20.128
and guess whose name
is on that list.

15:20.170 --> 15:21.880
Ahmad Hadid.
Exactly.

15:21.921 --> 15:23.923
So she wasn't just
a specialist on Hadid.

15:23.965 --> 15:25.050
She was also
his handler.

15:25.091 --> 15:26.593
Yeah, correct.

15:26.634 --> 15:28.511
It seems that back in the day,
the CIA wanted to try

15:28.553 --> 15:30.722
to develop
a relationship with Hadid.

15:30.764 --> 15:33.683
Look. Here's an interview
that she conducted

15:33.725 --> 15:36.353
with Hadid early on
in his recruitment.

15:36.394 --> 15:38.855
Let's go back to 2001.

15:38.897 --> 15:40.648
You said
that after the invasion,

15:40.690 --> 15:43.485
there was a deep rift
within the organization.

15:43.526 --> 15:45.320
How did you
consolidate power?

15:45.362 --> 15:46.988
Hadid: By understanding
the people,

15:47.030 --> 15:50.033
what they'll fight for,
lay their lives down for.

15:50.075 --> 15:53.578
My opponents spoke
from here.

15:53.620 --> 15:55.288
I spoke from here.

15:55.330 --> 15:59.042
So you're good at manipulating
your followers.

15:59.084 --> 16:02.128
Getting them to do
what you want.

16:02.170 --> 16:03.755
No.

16:03.797 --> 16:06.591
They already have
these passions inside them.

16:06.633 --> 16:08.968
I just know how to bring it
to the surface.

16:12.764 --> 16:15.266
Hang on.

16:15.308 --> 16:16.476
Is it just me,
or are you guys

16:16.518 --> 16:17.936
detecting a vibe
between these two?

16:17.977 --> 16:19.729
It's not just you.
I've seen perps

16:19.771 --> 16:21.690
try to charm their interviewers
like that before.

16:21.731 --> 16:22.857
Yeah, and going off
her body language,

16:22.899 --> 16:25.193
it looks like
it was working.

16:25.235 --> 16:26.444
I mean,
you don't think --

16:26.486 --> 16:27.654
Yeah, it would hardly be
the first romance

16:27.696 --> 16:29.197
between a handler
and an asset.

16:29.239 --> 16:31.866
It would explain why Nadine
wants to avenge Hadid's death.

16:31.908 --> 16:33.827
Indeed. I mean, first
they have her cultivate

16:33.868 --> 16:36.538
Hadid as an asset,
then the political winds change,

16:36.579 --> 16:37.789
and they order him killed.

16:37.831 --> 16:39.165
I mean, if she had
fallen for him,

16:39.207 --> 16:41.209
that would definitely send her
off the deep end.

16:41.251 --> 16:45.588
Yeah, but we took out Hadid
over seven years ago.

16:45.630 --> 16:48.008
Why wait until now to do
something about it?

16:48.049 --> 16:50.760
**

16:50.802 --> 16:53.179
[ Birds cawing,
wings flapping ]

16:53.221 --> 16:54.848
[ Groans ]

16:54.889 --> 17:04.482
**

17:04.524 --> 17:14.367
**

17:14.409 --> 17:15.952
[ Cellphone beeps ]

17:15.994 --> 17:23.001
**

17:23.043 --> 17:29.841
**

17:29.883 --> 17:33.053
Come on, come on, come on.

17:33.094 --> 17:34.429
[ Cellphone beeps ]

17:34.471 --> 17:40.769
**

17:40.810 --> 17:46.941
**

17:46.983 --> 17:51.071
Suzy, Joy...

17:51.112 --> 17:52.739
Um, it looks like

17:52.781 --> 17:57.535
I've gotten myself
into a bit of a situation here.

17:57.577 --> 18:01.164
And, well,
if you're seeing this,

18:01.206 --> 18:05.335
I guess it means
things didn't really go my way.

18:05.377 --> 18:14.719
**

18:14.761 --> 18:17.097
I've got trail mix,
a granola bar,

18:17.138 --> 18:18.973
and an orange soda.

18:19.015 --> 18:21.309
Thanks, but I'm not
really hungry.

18:21.351 --> 18:29.776
**

18:29.818 --> 18:31.653
You wanna talk about it?

18:33.154 --> 18:35.448
Talk about what?

18:35.490 --> 18:37.659
It's been over nine hours
since he went into surgery,

18:37.701 --> 18:39.202
and they still haven't
said anything.

18:39.244 --> 18:43.415
I'm not talking about TC.
I'm talking about you.

18:43.456 --> 18:45.166
How are youdoing?

18:48.503 --> 18:50.213
I-I just...

18:53.258 --> 18:56.511
No one else has been there
for me the way he has,

18:56.553 --> 18:59.472
and now...

18:59.514 --> 19:01.307
I know.
Sweetie, I know.

19:01.349 --> 19:07.564
**

19:07.605 --> 19:09.899
[ Exciting music plays ]

19:09.941 --> 19:12.027
**

19:12.068 --> 19:14.112
[ Gauge beeping ]

19:14.154 --> 19:17.115
Air support, this is Mike
Five Five Six Mike Hotel.

19:17.157 --> 19:19.451
I'm heading back to refuel.
Over.

19:19.492 --> 19:20.785
HPD Air Support:
Copy that.

19:23.038 --> 19:25.832
Air support, Mike Five Five
Six Mike Hotel again.

19:25.874 --> 19:28.376
I-I've just spotted
our suspect vehicle.

19:28.418 --> 19:31.338
Repeat -- I've got eyes
on our suspect vehicle!

19:31.379 --> 19:36.634
**

19:36.676 --> 19:38.636
[ Dogs barking in distance ]

19:38.678 --> 19:46.436
**

19:46.478 --> 19:47.896
Over here.

19:47.937 --> 19:51.733
[ Barking continues ]

19:51.775 --> 19:53.651
They got a scent!

19:53.693 --> 20:02.952
**

20:06.790 --> 20:09.417
[ Exciting music plays ]

20:09.459 --> 20:13.630
**

20:13.672 --> 20:15.632
[ Dogs barking ]

20:15.674 --> 20:23.640
**

20:23.682 --> 20:31.690
**

20:31.731 --> 20:39.739
**

20:39.781 --> 20:47.539
**

20:47.580 --> 20:49.124
[ Cellphone chimes ]
Well, that's interesting.

20:49.165 --> 20:51.668
What is it?
Nadine Amherst has a child,

20:51.710 --> 20:53.294
a son born in 2015.

20:53.336 --> 20:56.256
That's, what, a year after
she started cultivating Hadid?

20:56.297 --> 20:58.675
Well, based on the timeline,
that couldbe Hadid's son.

20:58.717 --> 21:00.802
Yeah, if we're right about them
mingling romantically,

21:00.844 --> 21:02.303
that seems so.

21:02.345 --> 21:05.724
I'm gonna see if I can find
any photos of the child online

21:05.765 --> 21:07.559
that might confirm
our hunch.

21:07.600 --> 21:09.436
[ Cellphone beeps ]

21:09.477 --> 21:10.979
What do you got?

21:11.021 --> 21:12.605
It's an obituary.

21:12.647 --> 21:13.857
Look -- Michael Amherst.

21:13.898 --> 21:17.027
He died last April
of MERS.

21:17.068 --> 21:18.319
That is a respiratory illness

21:18.361 --> 21:19.654
that's common
in Middle Eastern men.

21:19.696 --> 21:21.656
Well, he looks a hell of a lot
like Hadid.

21:21.698 --> 21:23.324
I mean,
that's gotta be his son.

21:23.366 --> 21:24.659
Right.
I mean, that would explain

21:24.701 --> 21:26.536
why Nadine didn't
seek revenge immediately.

21:26.578 --> 21:27.829
She had a son to care for.

21:27.871 --> 21:29.122
Right,
and when the kid died,

21:29.164 --> 21:30.415
it must've pushed her
over the edge.

21:30.457 --> 21:32.042
Suddenly she didn't have
much to live for.

21:32.083 --> 21:34.044
And nothing to lose.

21:34.794 --> 21:36.463
[ Cellphone beeps ]

21:36.504 --> 21:38.381
Yeah, we're coming up on the pin
that Shammy sent us.

21:38.423 --> 21:39.841
It's straight ahead.

21:39.883 --> 21:42.886
[ Engine revs ]

21:42.927 --> 21:45.221
[ Police radio chatter ]

21:45.263 --> 21:50.810
**

21:50.852 --> 21:56.399
**

21:56.441 --> 21:58.526
Hope you know
we're joining the search.

21:58.568 --> 21:59.861
Wouldn't expect any less.

21:59.903 --> 22:01.279
Good to see you, sir.

22:01.321 --> 22:03.531
[ Siren wails in distance ]

22:03.573 --> 22:04.866
All right, listen up.

22:04.908 --> 22:07.077
Our subject's name
is Orville Wright, goes by Rick.

22:07.118 --> 22:08.495
He's on foot,
possibly injured.

22:08.536 --> 22:09.871
Now, taking into account

22:09.913 --> 22:11.498
the approximate time
of the car wreck,

22:11.539 --> 22:14.626
we're looking at a search radius
of roughly 10 to 20 miles.

22:14.668 --> 22:17.629
It's also likely that we are not
the only ones looking for him,

22:17.671 --> 22:20.006
so stay sharp and stay safe.

22:20.048 --> 22:21.549
And remember,

22:21.591 --> 22:24.219
these are the same people
that killed Detective Childs.

22:24.260 --> 22:25.970
They are armed and dangerous.

22:26.012 --> 22:29.557
So if you see them,
shoot to kill.

22:29.599 --> 22:31.685
Let's go find him.

22:31.726 --> 22:34.396
[ Sirens wailing ]

22:40.276 --> 22:42.570
He's out of surgery
and stable.

22:42.612 --> 22:44.864
Oh, thank God.

22:44.906 --> 22:47.075
So he's gonna be okay?

22:47.117 --> 22:49.577
We've managed to extract
all of the bullet fragments.

22:49.619 --> 22:51.663
But Mr. Calvin has
a lacerated spleen,

22:51.705 --> 22:54.416
fractured ribs,
and extensive tissue damage.

22:54.457 --> 22:57.669
The road to recovery
will be long and challenging.

22:57.711 --> 22:59.462
That said, he's made it
through the worst of it,

22:59.504 --> 23:02.966
so there is reason
for cautious optimism.

23:05.885 --> 23:07.679
That's good news, okay?

23:11.182 --> 23:12.600
Can we see him?

23:12.642 --> 23:14.102
We still have a bunch
of tests to run,

23:14.144 --> 23:15.437
but as soon as he can
take visitors,

23:15.478 --> 23:16.896
we'll let you know,
okay?

23:16.938 --> 23:18.440
Thank you, Doctor.

23:20.734 --> 23:22.777
[ Sighs ]

23:22.819 --> 23:25.113
[ Down-tempo music plays ]

23:25.155 --> 23:27.449
[ Monitor beeping ]

23:27.490 --> 23:32.454
**

23:32.495 --> 23:34.539
Hey, how you feeling,
Mr. Calvin?

23:35.498 --> 23:38.793
[ Scoffs ]
Like I've been shot.

23:38.835 --> 23:43.214
I suppose
that's to be expected.

23:43.256 --> 23:48.011
My friends, Thomas Magnum
and Orville Wright --

23:48.053 --> 23:49.429
they could've been
targeted, too.

23:49.471 --> 23:51.848
I need to find out
if they're okay.

23:51.890 --> 23:55.226
I'll try to find someone who can
get you that information.

23:55.268 --> 23:58.480
Right now, I need
to examine you, okay?

23:58.521 --> 23:59.314
All right.

23:59.356 --> 24:01.191
Lift your arms for me.

24:05.862 --> 24:07.739
Push against my hand.

24:07.781 --> 24:08.948
[ Grunts ]

24:08.990 --> 24:11.576
Good.
All right.

24:11.618 --> 24:14.537
Now, take my hand,
try to squeeze.

24:14.579 --> 24:21.503
**

24:21.544 --> 24:28.301
**

24:28.343 --> 24:30.929
Can you feel that?

24:30.970 --> 24:34.224
No.
I can't feel anything.

24:36.768 --> 24:38.978
My legs.

24:39.020 --> 24:41.106
I can't move them.

24:41.147 --> 24:42.649
Try not to panic.

24:42.691 --> 24:46.194
Now, there's likely swelling
around the spinal cord.

24:46.236 --> 24:47.821
But with the right treatment
and physical therapy,

24:47.862 --> 24:51.574
there's a good chance
you'll regain mobility.

24:51.616 --> 24:53.368
Good chance?

24:53.410 --> 24:56.788
Are you saying I might not
ever walk again?

24:56.830 --> 24:58.456
I realize this is a lot
to take in,

24:58.498 --> 25:01.918
but let's not get ahead
of ourselves, okay?

25:01.960 --> 25:05.630
**

25:09.467 --> 25:11.594
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

25:11.636 --> 25:16.391
**

25:16.433 --> 25:19.352
Hey, what are you
thinking?

25:19.394 --> 25:20.729
That he would've sought
the densest cover

25:20.770 --> 25:23.023
to avoid being seen,
so we should keep this heading.

25:23.064 --> 25:25.191
No. I mean...

25:25.233 --> 25:26.985
you're clearly agonizing
over something.

25:27.027 --> 25:29.487
You should just tell me.

25:33.074 --> 25:35.368
Ah.

25:35.410 --> 25:37.746
You were right.

25:37.787 --> 25:40.415
I should've taken the threat
more serious.

25:40.457 --> 25:42.751
I should've done more
to protect Rick and TC.

25:42.792 --> 25:46.171
Thomas,
they're grown adults.

25:46.212 --> 25:47.547
They can look after
themselves.

25:47.589 --> 25:49.049
And -- And in fact,
they did.

25:49.090 --> 25:52.385
TC upped his security.
Even Rick took precautions.

25:52.427 --> 25:55.263
Yeah, well, the irony's
not lost on me.

25:55.305 --> 25:56.556
What irony?

25:56.598 --> 25:58.058
I did next to nothing
to protect myself,

25:58.099 --> 26:01.061
and I might be the only one
that makes it through this okay.

26:01.102 --> 26:03.229
But, Thomas,
it's not your fault.

26:03.271 --> 26:06.316
It's not about that.
It's not about blame.

26:06.358 --> 26:08.818
So what is it about?

26:08.860 --> 26:10.612
Back in Afghanistan,
after we were captured,

26:10.653 --> 26:12.489
there was no good reason
to think

26:12.530 --> 26:14.491
we'd make it
out of there alive.

26:14.532 --> 26:17.243
The only thing we had going
for us was each other.

26:17.285 --> 26:21.581
If somebody got low, the rest
of us would pick him up, right?

26:21.623 --> 26:23.875
Because individually,

26:23.917 --> 26:25.752
there's no way any of us
would've survived that,

26:25.794 --> 26:29.255
but as a group, it felt like
there was no way we wouldn't.

26:29.297 --> 26:32.467
Now, you form a bond when you go
through something like that,

26:32.509 --> 26:34.886
a bond you assume
can never be broken.

26:34.928 --> 26:37.597
That bond survived
Nuzo dying.

26:37.639 --> 26:41.810
But if Rick or TC
don't make it through this,

26:41.851 --> 26:45.188
I-I just...

26:45.230 --> 26:48.274
I don't know
what's left of it.

26:48.316 --> 26:51.277
Well, when you put it
like that,

26:51.319 --> 26:53.488
yeah, I-I understand
completely.

26:55.407 --> 26:57.325
You have to have faith.

27:01.830 --> 27:03.331
Thomas?

27:03.373 --> 27:04.958
You hear that?

27:05.000 --> 27:07.335
[ Water trickling ]

27:10.130 --> 27:11.798
If he heard this stream,
he would've come this way

27:11.840 --> 27:14.259
and then walked
through the water

27:14.300 --> 27:16.761
to avoid
leaving footprints.

27:16.803 --> 27:20.515
Agreed.
Upstream or downstream?

27:20.557 --> 27:22.517
I mean,
it's gotta be upstream.

27:22.559 --> 27:23.935
Right?
He was a Marine Scout Sniper.

27:23.977 --> 27:26.646
Finding the high ground
comes as second nature.

27:29.065 --> 27:31.317
[ Knock on door ]

27:31.359 --> 27:34.946
Hey, you up
for some visitors?

27:34.988 --> 27:37.866
Of course.

27:37.907 --> 27:40.160
Oh!

27:40.201 --> 27:42.746
Oh, thank God
you're okay.

27:42.787 --> 27:45.665
I don't think I've ever been
more worried in my life.

27:45.707 --> 27:47.584
Yeah, I'm sorry
about that.

27:50.795 --> 27:52.547
Really, dude?

27:52.589 --> 27:55.258
Kumu just tried to get
to second base with me.

27:55.300 --> 27:58.053
The least you could do
is dap me up.

27:58.094 --> 28:00.347
Sorry.

28:00.388 --> 28:04.059
It's just a lot to take in,
you know?

28:07.270 --> 28:08.646
I do.

28:10.607 --> 28:12.984
I still got a lot
of recovering to do.

28:15.362 --> 28:17.072
It's gonna take all I got.

28:18.990 --> 28:22.660
I need you to be strong
for me, too.

28:22.702 --> 28:24.579
Think you can do that?

28:26.164 --> 28:28.041
Yeah.
Of course.

28:29.292 --> 28:30.877
Do you really
have to ask?

28:32.879 --> 28:34.589
Good.

28:37.926 --> 28:40.303
Now, there's something
I gotta tell you guys.

28:40.345 --> 28:46.059
**

28:46.101 --> 28:47.769
Footprints.

28:51.106 --> 28:52.816
It's up this way.

28:52.857 --> 29:01.533
**

29:01.574 --> 29:04.411
Looks like the trail
ends here.

29:04.452 --> 29:06.162
Somebody dropped a phone.

29:06.204 --> 29:14.295
**

29:14.337 --> 29:17.340
It's -- It's Rick's.

29:17.382 --> 29:19.426
There's two sets
of ATV tracks.

29:19.467 --> 29:24.014
**

29:24.055 --> 29:25.640
Look at here.

29:28.143 --> 29:29.853
That's blood.

29:31.021 --> 29:33.148
Rick tried to fend them off,
but they grabbed him.

29:33.189 --> 29:36.776
[ Grunting ]

29:36.818 --> 29:40.572
I'm gonna try and radio Gordie,
tell them to look out for ATVs.

29:40.613 --> 29:47.120
**

29:47.162 --> 29:53.418
**

29:53.460 --> 29:55.754
Suzy, Joy...

29:55.795 --> 29:57.630
Um, it looks like

29:57.672 --> 30:00.467
I got myself
into a bit of a situation here.

30:00.508 --> 30:02.802
And if you're seeing this,

30:02.844 --> 30:04.971
well, it means things...

30:05.013 --> 30:08.183
well, they didn't go my way.

30:08.224 --> 30:10.935
But whatever happens,

30:10.977 --> 30:15.148
I just need you both to know
how important you are to me.

30:15.190 --> 30:17.525
Um, Joy, uh,

30:17.567 --> 30:21.363
I've only been your daddy now
for a couple months,

30:21.404 --> 30:24.324
and, um...

30:24.366 --> 30:28.828
you are the greatest
accomplishment of my life.

30:28.870 --> 30:32.082
Though I suppose your mom
is part of the reason

30:32.123 --> 30:35.710
you turned out
as awesome as you did.

30:35.752 --> 30:39.464
And, Suzy...

30:39.506 --> 30:42.592
I love you.

30:42.634 --> 30:44.844
I-I'm in love with you,
and --

30:44.886 --> 30:46.846
and I-I'm pretty sure
I've been in love with you

30:46.888 --> 30:48.890
since the moment I met you.

30:51.351 --> 30:53.478
My only regret is that

30:53.520 --> 30:56.398
I didn't get a chance
to tell you in person.

30:56.439 --> 30:57.649
[ Cellphone beeps off ]

30:57.691 --> 31:00.193
[ Footsteps approaching ]

31:02.195 --> 31:05.365
Thomas?

31:05.407 --> 31:07.951
Yeah, yeah.
What did Gordie say?

31:07.992 --> 31:12.122
He said that no one's seen
any ATVs as of yet.

31:12.163 --> 31:14.541
But we can't lose hope.

31:14.582 --> 31:15.875
We still have Swayzak
in custody,

31:15.917 --> 31:18.461
and he's our best bet
at getting to Nadine.

31:18.503 --> 31:27.012
**

31:27.053 --> 31:35.353
**

31:35.395 --> 31:37.397
[ Tires screech ]

31:37.439 --> 31:40.066
[ Indistinct shouting ]

31:40.108 --> 31:42.569
[ Gunshots ]

31:42.610 --> 31:50.952
**

31:50.994 --> 31:52.871
U.S. Marshall:
Come on, let's go.

31:55.540 --> 31:56.916
Nadine sent me.

31:56.958 --> 32:00.253
There's a white SUV
parked 100 yards back.

32:00.295 --> 32:02.088
Keys are under the visor.

32:02.130 --> 32:03.923
Take it and go.

32:09.679 --> 32:11.389
[ Suspenseful music plays ]

32:11.431 --> 32:13.516
[ Metal door slams ]

32:13.558 --> 32:18.938
**

32:18.980 --> 32:24.486
**

32:24.527 --> 32:25.987
You know who I am?

32:27.697 --> 32:30.158
Nadine Amherst.

32:30.200 --> 32:33.328
I gotta say, you're a lot less
dead than I expected.

32:33.370 --> 32:34.621
[ Chuckles ]

32:34.662 --> 32:38.083
And you're even more resilient
than I expected.

32:39.959 --> 32:42.170
So you fake your own death

32:42.212 --> 32:44.214
and you start going
after the people

32:44.255 --> 32:47.842
that are responsible
for killing Hadid?

32:47.884 --> 32:50.387
What was he to you?

32:50.428 --> 32:52.180
So many things,

32:52.222 --> 32:56.184
including the father of my son,
Michael.

32:56.226 --> 33:00.980
That boy was always so curious
about his father.

33:01.022 --> 33:04.651
Wanted to know everything
about the man.

33:04.693 --> 33:08.863
But there was one question
I could never answer for him.

33:08.905 --> 33:11.199
I read the action report.

33:11.241 --> 33:13.368
I know you're the one
that pulled the trigger.

33:13.410 --> 33:17.664
But we both know
that those reports are, uh,

33:17.706 --> 33:19.290
light on the details.

33:19.332 --> 33:22.377
You want to know
how he died.

33:22.419 --> 33:24.087
That's why
I'm still alive.

33:24.129 --> 33:27.090
Who better to answer that than
the man that took his life?

33:28.758 --> 33:31.511
So, how'd it happen?

33:33.013 --> 33:35.181
Well, I can't say
he didn't suffer.

33:37.100 --> 33:39.394
But he did
go out fighting.

33:41.396 --> 33:44.065
Is that so?

33:44.107 --> 33:46.693
That's what you want to hear,
right?

33:46.735 --> 33:47.902
He died a hero?

33:47.944 --> 33:50.447
What I want to hear
is the truth.

33:54.993 --> 33:56.369
Okay, then.

33:57.954 --> 33:59.706
Magnum:
This is team leader.

33:59.748 --> 34:02.417
We just breached the main gate,
heading to primary set point.

34:02.459 --> 34:04.252
T.S.: Heads up.
Uknowns gathering.

34:04.294 --> 34:05.837
Southwest corner.

34:05.879 --> 34:07.297
[ Indistinct conversation ]

34:07.339 --> 34:08.673
Magnum:
Light 'em up.

34:08.715 --> 34:10.091
[ Gunshots ]

34:10.133 --> 34:11.760
[ Grunts ]

34:11.801 --> 34:13.011
They have a gun!

34:13.053 --> 34:14.596
[ Gunshots, grunt ]

34:14.637 --> 34:19.893
**

34:19.934 --> 34:22.187
[ Gunshot, grunt ]

34:24.481 --> 34:26.107
[ Goat bleats ]

34:26.649 --> 34:28.902
Magnum: Charlie zero five,
proceed to primary.

34:28.943 --> 34:30.612
We'll hold position.

34:30.653 --> 34:32.238
Rick: Copy.

34:32.280 --> 34:34.532
[ Gunshot, grunt ]

34:34.574 --> 34:39.204
**

34:39.245 --> 34:41.539
[ Gunshot, grunt ]

34:41.581 --> 34:49.047
**

34:49.089 --> 34:51.633
Charlie zero five
proceeding to primary.

34:51.675 --> 34:59.933
**

34:59.974 --> 35:02.811
[ Bomb beeps and explodes ]

35:02.852 --> 35:05.313
[ Speaking native language ]

35:05.355 --> 35:07.107
[ Gunshot, grunt ]

35:07.148 --> 35:08.400
[ Body thuds ]

35:08.441 --> 35:10.443
All stations,
target secure.

35:12.445 --> 35:14.531
I don't know what you've told
yourself to justify

35:14.572 --> 35:16.616
getting into bed
with a terrorist.

35:16.658 --> 35:18.827
Maybe you thought he was
doing it for his people.

35:18.868 --> 35:21.663
But what kind of a man
uses an innocent woman

35:21.705 --> 35:22.747
as a human shield?

35:22.789 --> 35:24.499
You're lying.

35:24.541 --> 35:26.001
If you say so.

35:26.042 --> 35:30.338
I mean, you spent your entire
career interrogating people.

35:30.380 --> 35:35.093
If anybody can sniff out a lie,
it should be you.

35:35.135 --> 35:37.470
I guess there's only one way
to find out.

35:37.512 --> 35:43.685
**

35:43.727 --> 35:44.936
Where to begin?

35:44.978 --> 35:46.688
[ Tires screech in distance ]

35:48.314 --> 35:49.691
What's going on?

35:49.733 --> 35:53.111
A vehicle just pulled up.
We may need to move.

35:55.697 --> 35:58.033
Swayzak?
Thanks for springing me.

35:58.074 --> 36:00.410
What the hell are you
doing here?

36:00.452 --> 36:03.288
They let you escape
so they could follow you here.

36:04.581 --> 36:07.042
We need to
get out of here!

36:07.083 --> 36:08.251
Katsumoto: HPD!

36:08.293 --> 36:09.878
[ Indistinct shouting ]

36:09.919 --> 36:11.379
Get on your knees!
Now!

36:11.421 --> 36:14.132
[ Gunfire, grunting ]

36:14.174 --> 36:16.634
[ Indistinct shouting ]

36:16.676 --> 36:18.303
[ Exciting music plays ]

36:18.345 --> 36:19.929
Get on your knees!

36:19.971 --> 36:25.018
**

36:25.060 --> 36:27.062
Been looking for you.

36:27.103 --> 36:31.816
**

36:31.858 --> 36:33.902
[ Both grunting ]

36:33.943 --> 36:42.744
**

36:42.786 --> 36:51.586
**

36:51.628 --> 37:00.470
**

37:00.512 --> 37:09.104
**

37:09.145 --> 37:17.779
**

37:17.821 --> 37:21.366
[ Isak Danielson's
"Better Days" plays ]

37:21.408 --> 37:23.868
* There's a convo
right next to me *

37:23.910 --> 37:27.831
* But I just don't feel
like talking *

37:29.666 --> 37:33.253
* There's a woman
pouring her coffee *

37:33.294 --> 37:36.423
* And can't stop laughing *

37:38.383 --> 37:41.177
* I realize the little things *

37:41.219 --> 37:44.639
* Make me feel here,
make me present *

37:46.558 --> 37:50.228
* But then the sound
of a cigarette lit *

37:50.270 --> 37:52.856
* I think about Daniel *

37:55.734 --> 38:01.406
* Take the fire
and the flames *

38:04.200 --> 38:08.705
* Ooh, ooh, ooh, ooh *

38:08.747 --> 38:11.708
* Ooh *

38:12.876 --> 38:16.880
* Ooh, ooh, ooh *

38:16.921 --> 38:20.383
* Take the fire
and the flames *

38:20.425 --> 38:22.635
Excuse me, Doc, is this man
giving you trouble?

38:22.677 --> 38:26.014
No. In fact, I'm just
about done here.

38:26.056 --> 38:28.600
I'll go see about
getting you discharged.

38:30.852 --> 38:32.854
[ Sighs ]

38:32.896 --> 38:33.897
Where's Suzy?

38:33.938 --> 38:36.024
She went home
to relieve the sitter,

38:36.066 --> 38:37.233
check on the baby.

38:37.275 --> 38:39.194
Well, uh,
when you're done here,

38:39.235 --> 38:40.570
I can give you a ride back.

38:40.612 --> 38:42.906
No, thanks, man,
but I-I'm gonna go see TC

38:42.947 --> 38:44.157
after I get discharged.

38:44.199 --> 38:45.408
Well, you're gonna
have company.

38:45.450 --> 38:46.743
I was thinking of doing
the same thing.

38:46.785 --> 38:48.745
Oh, good, good.

38:48.787 --> 38:50.080
Hey.

38:50.121 --> 38:51.831
By the way, um...

38:55.585 --> 38:57.003
Thanks for saving my ass.

38:58.797 --> 39:00.298
Any time, any place.

39:00.340 --> 39:02.342
I appreciate it.

39:02.384 --> 39:04.719
But, hey,
if it's okay with you,

39:04.761 --> 39:06.805
I-I'd like to
not make it a habit...

39:06.846 --> 39:08.223
[ Laughs ]
...if that's okay.

39:08.264 --> 39:10.892
I was thinking
the same thing.

39:10.934 --> 39:12.519
Oh, uh...

39:14.312 --> 39:15.730
Almost forgot.

39:18.983 --> 39:20.610
I think this is yours.

39:20.652 --> 39:27.075
**

39:27.117 --> 39:29.035
Thanks.

39:29.077 --> 39:30.370
Yeah.

39:32.247 --> 39:34.124
I'll see you up there.

39:34.165 --> 39:39.254
**

39:39.295 --> 39:44.426
**

39:44.467 --> 39:46.761
[ Cellphone beeps ]

39:46.803 --> 39:56.563
**

39:56.604 --> 40:00.358
[ Indistinct conversations,
festive music playing ]

40:00.400 --> 40:01.985
Kumu: Hey.

40:02.027 --> 40:03.945
I figured I'd better
get a decent meal in him

40:03.987 --> 40:06.114
before he starts
to waste away.

40:06.156 --> 40:07.699
Good thinking.

40:07.741 --> 40:09.242
Can I get you
something?

40:09.284 --> 40:12.954
I'll have what he's having,
minus the animal flesh.

40:12.996 --> 40:14.789
Veggie burger coming up.

40:14.831 --> 40:16.082
Thank you.

40:16.124 --> 40:20.837
**

40:20.879 --> 40:23.840
So, you're probably pretty tired
of hearing this question,

40:23.882 --> 40:26.384
but, um,
how are you doing?

40:26.426 --> 40:30.180
**

40:30.221 --> 40:33.058
Okay, I guess.
Kumu's been awesome.

40:33.099 --> 40:37.187
She even offered to let me stay
with her until TC can come home.

40:37.228 --> 40:38.521
Well, that's great.

40:38.563 --> 40:40.398
Staying with Kumu
will be really fun.

40:40.440 --> 40:43.234
If you can keep up with her,
that is.

40:43.276 --> 40:44.319
[ Chuckles ]

40:44.361 --> 40:47.572
[ Dramatic music plays ]

40:47.614 --> 40:49.866
Everything is gonna be okay,
you know?

40:49.908 --> 40:53.953
**

40:53.995 --> 40:56.915
People have been telling me that
my whole life.

40:56.956 --> 40:59.918
But in my experience,
that's not always true.

40:59.959 --> 41:02.671
Sometimes people leave
and they never come back.

41:02.712 --> 41:05.840
Sometimes they get hurt
and they never get better.

41:05.882 --> 41:07.676
Sometimes things
don'tturn out okay,

41:07.717 --> 41:10.887
no matter how much you hope
and you pray that they might.

41:13.723 --> 41:17.310
I can't blame you
for feeling like that.

41:17.352 --> 41:19.396
But in this case,
you're wrong.

41:19.437 --> 41:21.856
Everything is
going to be okay.

41:23.608 --> 41:25.318
How can you be so sure?

41:25.360 --> 41:27.696
Because I know
these people.

41:27.737 --> 41:30.031
And you yourself know
how resilient TC is.

41:30.073 --> 41:32.033
[ Isak Danielson's
"Better Days" plays ]

41:32.075 --> 41:33.326
He has two friends...

41:33.368 --> 41:34.869
* Take the fire
and the flames *

41:34.911 --> 41:37.789
...who have been to hell
and back with him.

41:40.834 --> 41:43.003
* I'm much more peaceful
nowadays *

41:43.044 --> 41:46.881
Friends who are just
as strong as he is.

41:46.923 --> 41:49.259
And together, there is nothing
that they can't get through.

41:49.300 --> 41:53.513
* I can still say that
I miss you but not how you *

41:53.555 --> 41:58.018
* Didn't show up
when I needed you here *

41:58.059 --> 42:04.190
* Take the guilt
and take the pain *

42:04.232 --> 42:07.110
* 'Cause I'm moving on
to better days *

42:09.946 --> 42:19.914
**

42:19.956 --> 42:29.841
**

42:29.883 --> 42:39.809
**
